a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Pipefy is best suited for HR teams, procurement, service management, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Process Street, meanwhile, shines for operations teams, onboarding, compliance, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2014, Pipefy describes itself as \"AI-enhanced business process automation with customizable workflows.\" Process Street, established in 2014, positions itself as \"AI-powered workflow and checklist platform for recurring processes.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Pipefy** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 8), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Process Street is a poor choice — far from it. Process Street excels in its own right, particularly for operations teams and onboarding.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent pipe/kanban workflow model, go with Pipefy. If excellent for documenting and running processes matters more to you, Process Street is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
